news.title: Kochi: Rehabilitation package for GIFT City gets approval
news.para: According to the package, an amount of Rs 1.38 crore would be distributed to 98 persons, including 24 families, whose land and houses that would be acquired for the project.

news.title: Emaar India's director Hadi Badri resigns
news.para: “Due to my pre-occupation with other engagements, I am not in a position to devote my time to the affairs of the Company as a Director. Accordingly, I am submitting my resignation as director of the company with immediate effect,” Badri said in his resignation letter.

news.title: Walton Street BlackSoil debt fund invests Rs 75 crore in Shapoorji Pallonji's JV
news.para: The joint entity is developing a residential project in Mumbai’s Bandra (east) locality and the funds infused by WSBREDF-II will be utilized to complete the project.

news.title: Kanpur: KDA realizes Rs 2.62 crore compounding amount from Pragati Structures
news.para: It was a compounding amount which KDA had demanded last year but the builder company did not deposit the compounding amount and instead continued the construction work at the site.

news.title: Another private firm may be hired by Gurugram civic body for C&D waste collection
news.para: According to the MCG, an agreement between the corporation and a private company for collecting and transporting the C&D waste is currently on hold as the latter faces an inquiry for alleged fraud that it has denied.

news.title: Realtors in Rajasthan to get fee rebate to build homes for elders
news.para: Developers who will come forward to take these ‘retirement home’ scheme project will receive 100 per cent rebate in building plan fee, betterment levy and conversion charges.

news.title: Revenue from registries short of target in Noida for sixth straight year
news.para: Against the annual target of Rs 3,463 crore for fiscal 2021-2022, the department netted Rs 2,377 crore, which is around 68.6%.

news.title: Nashik civic body sends notices to 118 builders
news.para: The builders and developers had to transfer 20% of the flats to Maharashtra Housing Area Development Authority (Mhada) for economically weaker sections of the society, which is mandatory.

news.title: Macrotech Developers sales booking up 51% to Rs 9,024 crore in FY22
news.para: Among listed entities, Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, which markets its properties under Lodha brand, Godrej Properties, Bengaluru-based Prestige Estates and DLF are in the race to become the country's largest real estate developer in terms of sales bookings during the last financial year.

news.title: MahaRERA project data integration to prevent illegal property registrations
news.para: “This will be an inbuilt check. With this, registered projects’ MahaRERA number will automatically reflect in the survey number column to enable the citizens and officials to know if a project has been registered with the state real estate authority,” a senior MahaRERA official said on Wednesday.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso residents move SC say government has failed to protect interests
news.para: The petitioners told TOI they were exasperated by the delay in getting a structural audit of the condominium, where the hall areas of five flats in Tower D caved in on February 10, done by IIT-Delhi.

news.title: Patra Chawl redevelopment won't be hit by ED action: Maharashtra housing minister
news.para: In several SRA projects that have come under the ED lens, the land has been seized by the agency. Awhad said the 47 acres of Siddharth Nagar, of which Patra Chawl is a part (10 acres), is owned by Mhada, which is executing the project.

news.title: Delhi: Builders need to pay more labour cess
news.para: The labour department of Delhi government has revised the formula of calculating the cess for the first time since it was levied in January 2006. In the last 16 years, the government has collected more than Rs 3,400 crore from various construction activities.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group enters in strategic pact with state-owned firms
news.para: Analysts said Kaisa's move could set an example for other distressed property developers, including China Evergrande Group and Shimao Group, to introduce state-owned enterprises or local governments for their restructuring.

news.title: IndiQube raises $30 million from promoters & WestBridge Capital
news.para: It plans to use the proceeds, to double its PAN India commercial real estate footprint, venture into Tier II cities and to ramp up technology integration.
